# Visual Bible Feature — Auto Narrative Review for Historical Videos

When **Historical** constraint is checked, the app automatically generates a "Visual Bible" before processing segments.

## Proposed Changes

### Core Logic

---

#### [NEW] [narrative_review.py](file:///F:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/1.Prompt_Image/1.Prompt_Image/core/narrative_review.py)

- `generate_visual_bible(srt_path, api_client, log_callback) → str`: Read full SRT → send to API (**Pro** tier always) → return Visual Bible text
- `load_visual_bible(output_dir, project_name) → str | None`: Load cached file
- `save_visual_bible(output_dir, project_name, content)`: Save to `{project_name}_visual_bible.txt`

---

#### [NEW] [narrative_review_prompt.txt](file:///F:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/1.Prompt_Image/1.Prompt_Image/prompts/narrative_review_prompt.txt)

Prompt template instructing AI to produce structured context: historical period, main characters with descriptions, group characters (armies, civilians), architecture.

---

#### [MODIFY] [process_controller.py](file:///F:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/1.Prompt_Image/1.Prompt_Image/core/process_controller.py)

In [_process_single_project()](file:///F:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/1.Prompt_Image/1.Prompt_Image/core/process_controller.py#174-293), when `constraints.get("historical")` is True:
1. Try `load_visual_bible()` (use cache if exists)
2. If no cache → call `generate_visual_bible()` (Pro tier) and save
3. Pass Visual Bible text to [generate_batch()](file:///F:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/1.Prompt_Image/1.Prompt_Image/core/prompt_generator.py#211-243) as new parameter

---

#### [MODIFY] [prompt_generator.py](file:///F:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/1.Prompt_Image/1.Prompt_Image/core/prompt_generator.py)

- Add `visual_bible: str = ""` parameter to [generate_batch()](file:///F:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/1.Prompt_Image/1.Prompt_Image/core/prompt_generator.py#211-243), [_generate_sequential()](file:///F:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/1.Prompt_Image/1.Prompt_Image/core/prompt_generator.py#244-301), [generate_single()](file:///F:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/1.Prompt_Image/1.Prompt_Image/core/prompt_generator.py#101-155), [_build_user_message()](file:///F:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/1.Prompt_Image/1.Prompt_Image/core/prompt_generator.py#156-210)
- In [_build_user_message()](file:///F:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/1.Prompt_Image/1.Prompt_Image/core/prompt_generator.py#156-210): when visual_bible is provided, include as `=== VISUAL BIBLE (REFERENCE) ===` section with instruction to only use relevant info per segment

---

## Flow

```
User clicks Start (Historical ✓)
    │
    For each SRT project:
    ├─ Cached visual_bible exists? → load
    ├─ No cache? → API call (Pro) → generate → save file
    └─ Process segments with Visual Bible prepended to each request
```

## Verification

Manual testing: run app, check Historical, verify Visual Bible is generated/cached, and prompts include consistent character/setting descriptions.
